help.text: In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  ksmbd: fix use-after-free in session logoff  The sess->user object can currently be in use by another thread, for example if another connection has sent a session setup request to bind to the session being free'd. The handler for that connection could be in the smb2_sess_setup function which makes use of sess->user.
